### Key Classes

| Class | Module | Purpose |
|-------|--------|---------|
| `EPOCH` | `core` | Julian date calculations, time propagation |
| `RENDERER` | `renderer` | Abstract rendering interface (pure virtual) |
| `ANARI_RENDERER` | `renderer` | Concrete ANARI implementation of RENDERER. Constructor takes a library name string (e.g. `"halogen"`) and calls `anariLoadLibrary(name)` at runtime — the class is device-agnostic. No default; caller must specify. |
| `CAMERA_ORBIT` | `view` | Orbit camera parameters (theta, phi, distance, target) |
| `UpdateCameraOrbit` | `view` | Applies raw input deltas (nDX, nDY, dScrollY, mouse buttons) to CAMERA_ORBIT |
| `WASM_RUNTIME` | `wasm` | Wasmtime engine + store lifecycle (init/shutdown) |
| `SPV_PIPELINE` | `spirv` | SPIR-V validation (SPIRV-Tools) |
| `XR_RUNTIME` | `xr` | OpenXR loader lifecycle, instance creation, runtime discovery. Gracefully handles no-runtime case. |
| `HTTP_CLIENT` | `net` | libcurl lifecycle (global init/cleanup), synchronous HTTP GET, file download (`DownloadToFile`). Static lib with Schannel SSL. |
| `UI_CONTEXT` | `ui` | RmlUi lifecycle (init/shutdown). Provides stub system, render, and font engine interfaces. Real ANARI rendering deferred to SOM phase. |
| `GetEmbeddedKernel()` | `compute` | Retrieves SPIR-V bytecode embedded in the executable via Win32 resources. Returns pointer + size. |
| `COMPUTE_DISPATCH` | `compute` | Dispatches SPIR-V compute kernels via **Vox** (`vox::DEVICE::Create(Backend::Auto)` picks Vulkan / DX12 / Metal at construction). Falls back to registered CPU kernels when no GPU backend is available or Vox rejects the kernel. Built-in CPU fallback for `TEST_PROXIMITY`. The legacy `ANARIDevice` constructor parameter is retained for source compatibility but ignored. |
| `JWS_BASE` | `jws` | Shared core for JWS sign + verify. Static `Sign()` produces compact serialization with embedded `x5c` chain; instance `Verify()` validates the chain, checks the signature against the leaf's public key (via jwt-cpp), returns a `JWS_RESULT` struct (payload JSON, fingerprint, successor fingerprint, algorithm, error string). Supports RS256/384/512 and ES256/384/512. |
| `CERT_CHAIN` | `jws` | X.509 chain validation via BoringSSL's `X509_STORE`. Loads the Windows ROOT certificate store on Windows (`CertOpenSystemStoreA` + `CertEnumCertificatesInStore`), `X509_STORE_set_default_paths()` on Linux/macOS. Computes the leaf certificate's **public-key fingerprint** — `SHA-256(i2d_PUBKEY(leaf))` — which is the organizational identity used across the browser, the signing tool, and the HTML viewer. |
| `JWS_SERVICE` | `jws` | Derived from `JWS_BASE`. Typed accessors for MSS payloads: `GetNamespace()`, `GetOrganization()`, `GetServices()`, `GetModules()`, `GetSuccessor()`. Strongly-typed `MSS_SERVICE` and `MSS_MODULE` structs. |
| `JWS_FABRIC` | `jws` | Derived from `JWS_BASE`. Stubbed accessors for MSF payloads (`GetServiceRefs()`). The MSF payload schema is not yet fully defined — this class is a placeholder until the format stabilizes. |

**Naming note:** The concrete renderer class is `sneeze::renderer::ANARI_RENDERER`. The ANARI SDK's `ANARI_*` enum constants (e.g. `ANARI_RENDERER`, `ANARI_CAMERA`) live in the global namespace, so scoping ours inside `sneeze::renderer` avoids collision without needing a backend-specific class name. (An earlier iteration called the class `HELIDE_RENDERER` to dodge the collision; the namespace fix replaced that and lets the class carry a neutral name that reflects its device-agnostic nature.)

### Test Executables

**WasmTest.exe** — Standalone Wasmtime integration test suite (`tests/WasmRuntimeTest.cpp`). 21 assertions across 5 test groups, all passing:

| Test | What it proves |
|------|---------------|
| Engine + Store | Wasmtime library loads, engine and store construct and destruct cleanly |
| Compile + Call | Full pipeline: WAT text -> WASM bytes -> compiled module -> instance -> exported function call -> correct result (`add(3, 4) == 7`) |
| Fuel metering | CPU budget enforcement: `spin(10)` succeeds and consumes fuel, `spin(1000000)` with 5 fuel correctly traps. This is the mechanism Sneeze will use for per-service CPU budgets. |
| Error handling | Invalid WAT is rejected with a diagnostic message, no crash |
| Host functions | WASM-to-C++ callback: module imports `host.multiply`, Sneeze provides the implementation, `square(7)` returns 49. This is how the browser will expose its host API surface to sandboxed service code. |

**SpvTest.exe** — Standalone SPIR-V integration test suite (`tests/SpvPipelineTest.cpp`). Assertions across 4 test groups, all passing:

| Test | What it proves |
|------|---------------|
| Assemble | SPIRV-Tools can assemble SPIR-V text (human-readable assembly) into binary bytecode. Validates magic number (0x07230203). |
| Validate (good) | Valid compute shader passes SPIR-V validation against Vulkan 1.3 rules. |
| Validate (bad) | Garbage bytecode with valid magic number is correctly rejected — no crash, clean error path. |
| Disassemble | Round-trips binary back to text. Confirms OpEntryPoint and OpReturn survive the assembler/disassembler cycle. |

**XrTest.exe** — Standalone OpenXR integration test suite (`tests/XrRuntimeTest.cpp`). 10 assertions across 5 test groups, all passing:

| Test | What it proves |
|------|---------------|
| Version constants | OpenXR SDK headers are correct: major 1, minor >= 1, patch 58 (release-1.1.58). |
| Enumerate API layers | `xrEnumerateApiLayerProperties` succeeds (loader-level call, no runtime needed). Reports installed API layers (0 if none). |
| Enumerate extensions | `xrEnumerateInstanceExtensionProperties` is called. If no runtime is installed, the call returns error code -51 (`XR_ERROR_RUNTIME_UNAVAILABLE`), which is expected — no crash. If a runtime is present, lists available extensions. |
| Create instance | Full instance lifecycle: create, query properties (runtime name + version), query HMD system, query handheld display system, destroy. Each step gracefully handles the no-runtime case with a clean error code instead of a crash. On machines with SteamVR/Oculus/WMR installed, reports the runtime name, HMD capabilities, and tracking properties. |
| Struct initialization | Verifies OpenXR typed-struct pattern (`type` tag, `next` pointer, `flags`) works correctly with MSVC. |

